{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-05048/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-05048"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:50:48"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, pan"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Duration"]},"value":{"none":["long take"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman distressingly places a hand to her temple as a man adjusts the dress he alters on her."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-05048","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-05048"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/canvas/1/3135103e-9273-4d12-9a9e-c190038cd8b7","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T19:51:11.352Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Barbara Rose is crowded at the edge of the frame, echoing the suffocation she expresses as she grabs her neck and the cowl of the dress.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:151.94562407680993,240.9388847858195,660.6674667651403,754.680576070901"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/canvas/1/8241cd13-9f51-476c-80d9-38c53dfe54cb","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T19:51:34.802Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>While fitting the dress, Reynolds at one point pulls the fabric of the neckline up, so it completely obscures Barbara’s face. A few seconds later, when she, in discomfort, pulls the neckline down, he becomes frustrated. This moment speaks to his general attitude towards his craft. He cares much more about the dress, the object, than the person wearing it. He seemingly would prefer the person not have their own wants or feelings at all, and instead be a canvas for his art.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1292.8291174298379,134.83659527326412,536.9714734121121,846.4226366322008"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/canvas/1/79fe0cc8-e27d-4397-b1af-3e27861e8813","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T19:52:03.368Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The real-life inspiration for Barbara Rose, heiress Barbara Hutton, said the following during a press conference on the occasion of her marriage to playboy Porfirio Rubirosa: “I could never give anyone credit for loving me for myself . . . I hate to look in the mirror because I’m so ugly. I used to be beautiful. But I’m not anymore” (Haymann, <em>Poor Little Rich Girl</em>, 296).</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05048/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:29.371307237814506,32.95097858197895,243.29302067946833,171.92115952732647"}}}]}]}]}